parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause a loss of brake fluid, leading to poor brake performance, which can increase the stopping distance and risk of accidents.
Worn-out rear brake drums can cause poor brake performance, leading to increased stopping distances and a higher risk of accidents.
symptoms: grinding or screeching noise when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter system can cause the vehicle to not start, leaving the driver stranded, and potentially causing safety issues in certain situations, such as being stuck in traffic or in a hazardous location.
symptoms: the starter motor makes excessive noise
the starter motor does not engage
the vehicle has a clicking sound when trying to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loose transaxle shaft/rear axle seals can cause the differential seal to leak, leading to premature wear on the rear axle and differential components, and potentially causing loss of vehicle control or accidents.
Failure of the CV boot can cause premature wear on the CV joint, leading to noise, vibration, and steering problems, which can affect vehicle handling and safety.
Transmission delays when shifting up or down can cause loss of power, hesitation, or stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission delays when shifting up or down
transmission stays in gear too long before shifting
